============================================================
  QUESTION & ANSWER PAIRS
============================================================

Q1: What is entropy?
A1: Entropy measures disorder or randomness in a system.
     The Second Law of Thermodynamics states it always
     increases in isolated systems — the arrow of time.

Q2: What is democracy?
A2: Democracy is government where power derives from the
     people through free elections, rule of law, and
     protection of minority rights. Types include direct and
     representative democracy.

Q3: What is a neuron?
A3: A neuron is a nerve cell that processes and transmits
     information through electrical and chemical signals.
     Key parts: dendrites (receive signals), cell body, axon
     (send signals).

Q4: What is osmosis?
A4: Osmosis is the movement of water across a semi-
     permeable membrane from high water concentration to low
     water concentration (high solute to low solute) until
     equilibrium.

Q5: What is inflation?
A5: Inflation is the general rise in price levels over
     time, reducing purchasing power. Caused by excess money
     supply, high demand, or supply shocks. Measured by the
     Consumer Price Index.

